First we could simplify the terms $(2x)^4$ and $(3x)(x^3)$ separately: we have $(2x)^4 = 2^4x^4 = 16x^4$ and $(3x)(x^3) = 3x(x^3) = 3x^4$. Therefore, \begin{align*}
(2x)^4 + (3x)(x^3)&= 16x^4 + 3x^4
\end{align*}Combining like terms, we find \begin{align*}
16x^4 + 3x^4 &= \boxed{19x^4}.
\end{align*}
